# Cloudflare Pages redirects / rewrites for the AlbaBiz SPA.
#
# Pages serves real static files first (/styles.css, /app.js, /icons.js,
# /metrics.js, /config.js, /i18n.js, /fonts/*, /privatesia.html, /brand-mark.svg,
# /robots.txt, etc.), so those are unaffected by the rules below.
#
# For every OTHER path (the SPA's client-side routes: /biznes/<slug>,
# /kategoria/<slug>, /kontea/<slug>, /regjistro, /hiq) we must serve the app
# shell with a 200 *rewrite* (NOT a 3xx redirect) so the History-API router in
# app.js can take over on a hard refresh or shared/deep link.
#
# Per-route rules proved unreliable: Pages' default trailing-slash handling
# 308-redirected bare paths (e.g. /regjistro -> /) before an exact-match rule
# could fire. A single catch-all is the robust SPA pattern.

# Admin SPA keeps its own shell under /admin (gate with Cloudflare Access).
/admin           /admin/index.html   200
/admin/*         /admin/index.html   200

# Public SPA: any unmatched path serves the public shell (200 rewrite).
/*               /index.html         200
